And I explained:

If you look under the hood of the industrial economy, you easily see why there is this counter-intuitive relationship between tax rates and economic growth. With high taxes, the only way to retain the bulk of the wealth created by a business is by reinvesting it in the business -- in plants, equipment, staff, research and development, new products and all the rest.
